&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time (37.5 hours per week) and part time hours available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Same Day Medical Assessment is looking to recruit Healthcare Support Workers to join our team. Applicants should be caring, enthusiastic, motivated and flexible with a drive to provide excellent patient care supporting our qualified nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SDMA is developing and expanding to continue to provide same day medical care for patients but to also include the assessment and rapid treatment for all medical admissions to the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teamwork and communication are essential to our success as a Unit. We have multiple admissions / transfers / discharges per day, so the pace is fast but rewarding. Many of our patients arrive to us acutely unwell and the satisfaction is immense when they become more stable and are discharged home the same day or transferred to a ward for their continued excellent care in the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nina Penkethman - Unit Manager / Advanced Nurse Practitioner or Steve Todd - Senior Staff Nurse, SDMA. Telephone: 01872 253277 / 252328&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
